{
  "title": "Lateralus: A Pipeline-Native Programming Language",
  "description": "Lateralus is a statically-typed, pipeline-native programming language with Hindley-Milner type inference, algebraic data types, structured concurrency, and an effect system tracking IO/Async/Unsafe. It compiles to four backends (C99, JavaScript, WebAssembly, and a Python reference implementation), ships a self-hosted lexer/parser/formatter, a 62-module standard library, and a companion bare-metal operating system (LateralusOS) written in itself. The toolchain includes a full LSP, three editor extensions (GrugBot420, Antikythera Digital, Lateralus Language), and is dual-published to the Visual Studio Marketplace and Open VSX with publisher-domain verification on lateralus.dev.",
